  "body": "In discussion with @zelig and @nagydani concern was raised that a high frequency setting in mutable resources and consequently omitting periods can be used to force a client querying for updates to spend unnecessary resources, akin to a DDOS attack.\r\n\r\nIt should be possible for the client to decide on a max amount of periods it will traverse before it drops the query.",
